01/08/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A prosecutor charged eight former Yugoslav soldiers Thursday (July 31st) with war crimes for allegedly killing ethnic Albanian civilians during the NATO air strikes against Yugoslavia in 1999. 
The indictment says the eight committed war crimes in killing 23 ethnic Albanians who entered Montenegro from Kosovo. 
(RTCG, AP, International Herald Tribune, BTA - 31/07/08)
